[From a medical and public health standpoint, this moderator sees no
reason to discontinue the current ban.

A photograph of the red-eared slider turtle, the small turtle
involved in this issue, is available at
<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red-eared_slider>. - Mod.LL]

[And for a somewhat different view on the ban, ProMED-mail veterinary
moderator Mod.TG had the following thoughts: "If the turtles are
really free of salmonella -- they should be allowed. Why should
government have to protect us from pet turtles? Wash your hands if
you want to keep turtles. Teach kids cleanliness and responsibility."

Unfortunately in the human public health sector, we have observed
that recommendations aimed at disease prevention are not always
adhered to, but legislation is. - Mod.MPP]
